                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" id="amateurdramatics_sng_1" hclass="sense" fkcefr="c2"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">the activity of producing and acting in plays for the theatre, by people who do it for pleasure, not as a job</span></span><div class="collapse" htag="div" hclass="collapse"><span class="unbox" unbox="cult" id="amateurdramatics_unbox_1" source="ald9_guide"><span class="box_title">Culture</span><span class="body"><span class="p"><span class="dh">Amateur dramatics</span> (known as 'am-dram') is very popular in Britain, where there are many amateur dramatics clubs, even in small towns and villages. They perform plays for local people, charging them a small amount in order to pay for the costumes, hall, etc. </span></span></span></div><span class="topic-g"><span class="prefix">Topics </span><a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/topic/film-and-theatre?level=c2" title="Topic film-and-theatre"><span class="topic" href="l2:culture:film_and_theatre?cefr=c2"><span class="topic_name">Film and theatre</span><span class="topic_cefr">c2</span></span></a><span class="sep">,</span> <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/topic/hobbies?level=c2" title="Topic hobbies"><span class="topic" href="l2:leisure:hobbies?cefr=c2"><span class="topic_name">Hobbies</span><span class="topic_cefr">c2</span></span></a></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
